title: Stripe API
description: The Stripe REST API. Please see https://stripe.com/docs/api for more details.

auth_username.label: Username (basicAuth)
auth_username.note: Basic HTTP authentication. Allowed headers-- Authorization: Basic <api_key> | Authorization: Basic <base64 hash of `api_key:`>

auth_password.label: Password (basicAuth)
auth_password.note: Basic HTTP authentication. Allowed headers-- Authorization: Basic <api_key> | Authorization: Basic <base64 hash of `api_key:`>

auth_bearerAuth.label: bearerAuth (auth-scheme)
auth_bearerAuth.note: Bearer HTTP authentication. Allowed headers-- Authorization: Bearer <api_key>

GetAccount.title: GetAccount
GetAccount.description: Retrieves the details of an account.

GetAccountCapabilities.title: GetAccountCapabilities
GetAccountCapabilities.description:
Returns a list of capabilities associated with the account. The capabilities are
returned sorted by creation date, with the most recent capability appearing
first.

GetAccountExternalAccounts.title: GetAccountExternalAccounts
GetAccountExternalAccounts.description: List external accounts for an account.

GetAccountPeople.title: GetAccountPeople
GetAccountPeople.description:
Returns a list of people associated with the account's legal entity. The people
are returned sorted by creation date, with the most recent people appearing
first.

GetAccountPersons.title: GetAccountPersons
GetAccountPersons.description:
Returns a list of people associated with the account's legal entity. The people
are returned sorted by creation date, with the most recent people appearing
first.

GetAccounts.title: GetAccounts
GetAccounts.description:
Returns a list of accounts connected to your platform via Connect
[/docs/connect]. If you're not a platform, the list is empty.

GetAccountsAccountCapabilities.title: GetAccountsAccountCapabilities
GetAccountsAccountCapabilities.description:
Returns a list of capabilities associated with the account. The capabilities are
returned sorted by creation date, with the most recent capability appearing
first.

GetAccountsAccountExternalAccounts.title: GetAccountsAccountExternalAccounts
GetAccountsAccountExternalAccounts.description: List external accounts for an account.

GetAccountsAccountPeople.title: GetAccountsAccountPeople
GetAccountsAccountPeople.description:
Returns a list of people associated with the account's legal entity. The people
are returned sorted by creation date, with the most recent people appearing
first.

GetAccountsAccountPersons.title: GetAccountsAccountPersons
GetAccountsAccountPersons.description:
Returns a list of people associated with the account's legal entity. The people
are returned sorted by creation date, with the most recent people appearing
first.

GetApplicationFees.title: GetApplicationFees
GetApplicationFees.description:
Returns a list of application fees you've previously collected. The application
fees are returned in sorted order, with the most recent fees appearing first.

GetApplicationFeesIdRefunds.title: GetApplicationFeesIdRefunds
GetApplicationFeesIdRefunds.description:
You can see a list of the refunds belonging to a specific application fee. Note
that the 10 most recent refunds are always available by default on the
application fee object. If you need more than those 10, you can use this API
method and the limit and starting_after parameters to page through additional
refunds.

GetBalance.title: GetBalance
GetBalance.description:
Retrieves the current account balance, based on the authentication that was used
to make the request. For a sample request, see Accounting for negative balances
[/docs/connect/account-balances#accounting-for-negative-balances].

GetBalanceHistory.title: GetBalanceHistory
GetBalanceHistory.description:
Returns a list of transactions that have contributed to the Stripe account
balance (e.g., charges, transfers, and so forth).

GetBalanceTransactions.title: GetBalanceTransactions
GetBalanceTransactions.description:
Returns a list of transactions that have contributed to the Stripe account
balance (e.g., charges, transfers, and so forth).

GetBillingPortalConfigurations.title: GetBillingPortalConfigurations
GetBillingPortalConfigurations.description:
Returns a list of configurations that describe the functionality of the customer
portal.

GetBitcoinReceivers.title: GetBitcoinReceivers
GetBitcoinReceivers.description:
Returns a list of your receivers. Receivers are returned sorted by creation
date, with the most recently created receivers appearing first.

GetBitcoinReceiversReceiverTransactions.title: GetBitcoinReceiversReceiverTransactions
GetBitcoinReceiversReceiverTransactions.description: List bitcoin transacitons for a given receiver.

GetBitcoinTransactions.title: GetBitcoinTransactions
GetBitcoinTransactions.description: List bitcoin transacitons for a given receiver.

GetCharges.title: GetCharges
GetCharges.description:
Returns a list of charges you've previously created. The charges are returned in
sorted order, with the most recent charges appearing first.

GetChargesChargeDispute.title: GetChargesChargeDispute
GetChargesChargeDispute.description: Retrieve a dispute for a specified charge.

GetChargesChargeRefunds.title: GetChargesChargeRefunds
GetChargesChargeRefunds.description:
You can see a list of the refunds belonging to a specific charge. Note that the
10 most recent refunds are always available by default on the charge object.

GetCheckoutSessions.title: GetCheckoutSessions
GetCheckoutSessions.description: Returns a list of Checkout Sessions.

GetCheckoutSessionsSessionLineItems.title: GetCheckoutSessionsSessionLineItems
GetCheckoutSessionsSessionLineItems.description:
When retrieving a Checkout Session, there is an includable line_items property
containing the first handful of those items.

GetCountrySpecs.title: GetCountrySpecs
GetCountrySpecs.description: Lists all Country Spec objects available in the API.

GetCoupons.title: GetCoupons
GetCoupons.description: Returns a list of your coupons.

GetCreditNotes.title: GetCreditNotes
GetCreditNotes.description: Returns a list of credit notes.

GetCreditNotesPreview.title: GetCreditNotesPreview
GetCreditNotesPreview.description: Get a preview of a credit note without creating it.

GetCreditNotesPreviewLines.title: GetCreditNotesPreviewLines
GetCreditNotesPreviewLines.description:
When retrieving a credit note preview, you'll get a lines property containing
the first handful of those items.

GetCreditNotesCreditNoteLines.title: GetCreditNotesCreditNoteLines
GetCreditNotesCreditNoteLines.description:
When retrieving a credit note, you'll get a lines property containing the the
first handful of those items.

GetCustomers.title: GetCustomers
GetCustomers.description:
Returns a list of your customers. The customers are returned sorted by creation
date, with the most recent customers appearing first.

GetCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions.title: GetCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions
GetCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions.description:
Returns a list of transactions that updated the customer's balances
[/docs/billing/customer/balance].

GetCustomersCustomerBankAccounts.title: GetCustomersCustomerBankAccounts
GetCustomersCustomerBankAccounts.description:
You can see a list of the bank accounts belonging to a Customer. Note that the
10 most recent sources are always available by default on the Customer.

GetCustomersCustomerCards.title: GetCustomersCustomerCards
GetCustomersCustomerCards.description:
You can see a list of the cards belonging to a customer. Note that the 10 most
recent sources are always available on the Customer object.

GetCustomersCustomerPaymentMethods.title: GetCustomersCustomerPaymentMethods
GetCustomersCustomerPaymentMethods.description: Returns a list of PaymentMethods for a given Customer

GetCustomersCustomerSources.title: GetCustomersCustomerSources
GetCustomersCustomerSources.description: List sources for a specified customer.

GetCustomersCustomerSubscriptions.title: GetCustomersCustomerSubscriptions
GetCustomersCustomerSubscriptions.description:
You can see a list of the customer's active subscriptions. Note that the 10 most
recent active subscriptions are always available by default on the customer
object.

GetCustomersCustomerTaxIds.title: GetCustomersCustomerTaxIds
GetCustomersCustomerTaxIds.description: Returns a list of tax IDs for a customer.

GetDisputes.title: GetDisputes
GetDisputes.description: Returns a list of your disputes.

GetEvents.title: GetEvents
GetEvents.description:
List events, going back up to 30 days. Each event data is rendered according to
Stripe API version at its creation time.

GetExchangeRates.title: GetExchangeRates
GetExchangeRates.description:
Returns a list of objects that contain the rates at which foreign currencies are
converted to one another. Only shows the currencies for which Stripe supports.

GetFileLinks.title: GetFileLinks
GetFileLinks.description: Returns a list of file links.

GetFiles.title: GetFiles
GetFiles.description:
Returns a list of the files that your account has access to. The files are
returned sorted by creation date, with the most recently created files appearing
first.

GetInvoiceitems.title: GetInvoiceitems
GetInvoiceitems.description:
Returns a list of your invoice items. Invoice items are returned sorted by
creation date, with the most recently created invoice items appearing first.

GetInvoices.title: GetInvoices
GetInvoices.description:
You can list all invoices, or list the invoices for a specific customer. The
invoices are returned sorted by creation date, with the most recently created
invoices appearing first.

GetInvoicesUpcoming.title: GetInvoicesUpcoming
GetInvoicesUpcoming.description: At any time, you can preview the upcoming invoice for a customer.

GetInvoicesUpcomingLines.title: GetInvoicesUpcomingLines
GetInvoicesUpcomingLines.description:
When retrieving an upcoming invoice, you'll get a lines property containing the
total count of line items and the first handful of those items.

GetInvoicesInvoiceLines.title: GetInvoicesInvoiceLines
GetInvoicesInvoiceLines.description:
When retrieving an invoice, you'll get a lines property containing the total
count of line items and the first handful of those items. There is also a URL
where you can retrieve the full (paginated) list of line items.

GetIssuerFraudRecords.title: GetIssuerFraudRecords
GetIssuerFraudRecords.description: Returns a list of issuer fraud records.

GetIssuingAuthorizations.title: GetIssuingAuthorizations
GetIssuingAuthorizations.description:
Returns a list of Issuing Authorization objects. The objects are sorted in
descending order by creation date, with the most recently created object
appearing first.

GetIssuingCardholders.title: GetIssuingCardholders
GetIssuingCardholders.description:
Returns a list of Issuing Cardholder objects. The objects are sorted in
descending order by creation date, with the most recently created object
appearing first.

GetIssuingCards.title: GetIssuingCards
GetIssuingCards.description:
Returns a list of Issuing Card objects. The objects are sorted in descending
order by creation date, with the most recently created object appearing first.

GetIssuingDisputes.title: GetIssuingDisputes
GetIssuingDisputes.description:
Returns a list of Issuing Dispute objects. The objects are sorted in descending
order by creation date, with the most recently created object appearing first.

GetIssuingSettlements.title: GetIssuingSettlements
GetIssuingSettlements.description:
Returns a list of Issuing Settlement objects. The objects are sorted in
descending order by creation date, with the most recently created object
appearing first.

GetIssuingTransactions.title: GetIssuingTransactions
GetIssuingTransactions.description:
Returns a list of Issuing Transaction objects. The objects are sorted in
descending order by creation date, with the most recently created object
appearing first.

GetOrderReturns.title: GetOrderReturns
GetOrderReturns.description:
Returns a list of your order returns. The returns are returned sorted by
creation date, with the most recently created return appearing first.

GetOrders.title: GetOrders
GetOrders.description:
Returns a list of your orders. The orders are returned sorted by creation date,
with the most recently created orders appearing first.

GetPaymentMethods.title: GetPaymentMethods
GetPaymentMethods.description: Returns a list of PaymentMethods for a given Customer

GetPayouts.title: GetPayouts
GetPayouts.description:
Returns a list of existing payouts sent to third-party bank accounts or that
Stripe has sent you. The payouts are returned in sorted order, with the most
recently created payouts appearing first.

GetPlans.title: GetPlans
GetPlans.description: Returns a list of your plans.

GetPrices.title: GetPrices
GetPrices.description: Returns a list of your prices.

GetProducts.title: GetProducts
GetProducts.description:
Returns a list of your products. The products are returned sorted by creation
date, with the most recently created products appearing first.

GetPromotionCodes.title: GetPromotionCodes
GetPromotionCodes.description: Returns a list of your promotion codes.

GetQuotes.title: GetQuotes
GetQuotes.description: Returns a list of your quotes.

GetQuotesQuoteComputedUpfrontLineItems.title: GetQuotesQuoteComputedUpfrontLineItems
GetQuotesQuoteComputedUpfrontLineItems.description: When retrieving a quote, there is an includable computed.upfront.line_items

GetQuotesQuoteLineItems.title: GetQuotesQuoteLineItems
GetQuotesQuoteLineItems.description:
When retrieving a quote, there is an includable line_items property containing
the first handful of those items.

GetQuotesQuotePdf.title: GetQuotesQuotePdf
GetQuotesQuotePdf.description: Download the PDF for a finalized quote

GetRadarEarlyFraudWarnings.title: GetRadarEarlyFraudWarnings
GetRadarEarlyFraudWarnings.description: Returns a list of early fraud warnings.

GetRadarValueListItems.title: GetRadarValueListItems
GetRadarValueListItems.description:
Returns a list of ValueListItem objects. The objects are sorted in descending
order by creation date, with the most recently created object appearing first.

GetRadarValueLists.title: GetRadarValueLists
GetRadarValueLists.description:
Returns a list of ValueList objects. The objects are sorted in descending order
by creation date, with the most recently created object appearing first.

GetRecipients.title: GetRecipients
GetRecipients.description:
Returns a list of your recipients. The recipients are returned sorted by
creation date, with the most recently created recipients appearing first.

GetRefunds.title: GetRefunds
GetRefunds.description:
Returns a list of all refunds you've previously created. The refunds are
returned in sorted order, with the most recent refunds appearing first.

GetReportingReportRuns.title: GetReportingReportRuns
GetReportingReportRuns.description: Returns a list of Report Runs, with the most recent appearing first.

GetReportingReportTypes.title: GetReportingReportTypes
GetReportingReportTypes.description: Returns a full list of Report Types.

GetReviews.title: GetReviews
GetReviews.description:
Returns a list of Review objects that have open set to true. The objects are
sorted in descending order by creation date, with the most recently created
object appearing first.

GetSetupAttempts.title: GetSetupAttempts
GetSetupAttempts.description: Returns a list of SetupAttempts associated with a provided SetupIntent.

GetSigmaScheduledQueryRuns.title: GetSigmaScheduledQueryRuns
GetSigmaScheduledQueryRuns.description: Returns a list of scheduled query runs.

GetSkus.title: GetSkus
GetSkus.description:
Returns a list of your SKUs. The SKUs are returned sorted by creation date, with
the most recently created SKUs appearing first.

GetSourcesSourceSourceTransactions.title: GetSourcesSourceSourceTransactions
GetSourcesSourceSourceTransactions.description: List source transactions for a given source.

GetSubscriptionItems.title: GetSubscriptionItems
GetSubscriptionItems.description: Returns a list of your subscription items for a given subscription.

GetSubscriptionItemsSubscriptionItemUsag.title: GetSubscriptionItemsSubscriptionItemUsageRecordSummaries
GetSubscriptionItemsSubscriptionItemUsag.description: For the specified subscription item, returns a list of summary objects.

GetSubscriptionSchedules.title: GetSubscriptionSchedules
GetSubscriptionSchedules.description: Retrieves the list of your subscription schedules.

GetSubscriptions.title: GetSubscriptions
GetSubscriptions.description:
By default, returns a list of subscriptions that have not been canceled. In
order to list canceled subscriptions, specify status=canceled.

GetTaxCodes.title: GetTaxCodes
GetTaxCodes.description:
A list of all tax codes available [https://stripe.com/docs/tax/tax-codes] to add
to Products in order to allow specific tax calculations.

GetTaxRates.title: GetTaxRates
GetTaxRates.description:
Returns a list of your tax rates. Tax rates are returned sorted by creation
date, with the most recently created tax rates appearing first.

GetTerminalLocations.title: GetTerminalLocations
GetTerminalLocations.description: Returns a list of Location objects.

GetTerminalReaders.title: GetTerminalReaders
GetTerminalReaders.description: Returns a list of Reader objects.

GetTransfers.title: GetTransfers
GetTransfers.description:
Returns a list of existing transfers sent to connected accounts. The transfers
are returned in sorted order, with the most recently created transfers appearing
first.

GetTransfersIdReversals.title: GetTransfersIdReversals
GetTransfersIdReversals.description:
You can see a list of the reversals belonging to a specific transfer. Note that
the 10 most recent reversals are always available by default on the transfer
object.

GetWebhookEndpoints.title: GetWebhookEndpoints
GetWebhookEndpoints.description: Returns a list of your webhook endpoints.

DeleteAccount.title: DeleteAccount
DeleteAccount.description:
With Connect [/docs/connect], you can delete accounts you manage.

Accounts created using test-mode keys can be deleted at any time.

PostAccount.title: PostAccount
PostAccount.description:
Updates a connected account [/docs/connect/accounts] by setting the values of
the parameters passed. Any parameters not provided are left unchanged.

PostAccountBankAccounts.title: PostAccountBankAccounts
PostAccountBankAccounts.description: Create an external account for a given account.

DeleteAccountBankAccountsId.title: DeleteAccountBankAccountsId
DeleteAccountBankAccountsId.description: Delete a specified external account for a given account.

GetAccountBankAccountsId.title: GetAccountBankAccountsId
GetAccountBankAccountsId.description: Retrieve a specified external account for a given account.

PostAccountBankAccountsId.title: PostAccountBankAccountsId
PostAccountBankAccountsId.description:
Updates the metadata, account holder name, account holder type of a bank account
belonging to a Custom account.

GetAccountCapabilitiesCapability.title: GetAccountCapabilitiesCapability
GetAccountCapabilitiesCapability.description: Retrieves information about the specified Account Capability.

PostAccountExternalAccounts.title: PostAccountExternalAccounts
PostAccountExternalAccounts.description: Create an external account for a given account.

DeleteAccountExternalAccountsId.title: DeleteAccountExternalAccountsId
DeleteAccountExternalAccountsId.description: Delete a specified external account for a given account.

GetAccountExternalAccountsId.title: GetAccountExternalAccountsId
GetAccountExternalAccountsId.description: Retrieve a specified external account for a given account.

PostAccountExternalAccountsId.title: PostAccountExternalAccountsId
PostAccountExternalAccountsId.description:
Updates the metadata, account holder name, account holder type of a bank account
belonging to a Custom account [/docs/connect/custom-accounts],

PostAccountLoginLinks.title: PostAccountLoginLinks
PostAccountLoginLinks.description:
Creates a single-use login link for an Express account to access their Stripe
dashboard.

DeleteAccountPeoplePerson.title: DeleteAccountPeoplePerson
DeleteAccountPeoplePerson.description:
Deletes an existing person's relationship to the account's legal entity. Any
person with a relationship for an account can be deleted through the API, except
if the person is the account_opener.

DeleteAccountPersonsPerson.title: DeleteAccountPersonsPerson
DeleteAccountPersonsPerson.description:
Deletes an existing person's relationship to the account's legal entity. Any
person with a relationship for an account can be deleted through the API, except
if the person is the account_opener.

PostAccountLinks.title: PostAccountLinks
PostAccountLinks.description:
Creates an AccountLink object that includes a single-use Stripe URL that the
platform can redirect their user to in order to take them through the Connect
Onboarding flow.

PostAccounts.title: PostAccounts
PostAccounts.description:
With Connect [/docs/connect], you can create Stripe accounts for your users. To
do this, you'll first need to register your platform
[https://dashboard.stripe.com/account/applications/settings].

DeleteAccountsAccount.title: DeleteAccountsAccount
DeleteAccountsAccount.description:
With Connect [/docs/connect], you can delete accounts you manage.

Accounts created using test-mode keys can be deleted at any time. Custom or
Express accounts created using live-mode keys can only be deleted once all
balances are zero.

GetAccountsAccount.title: GetAccountsAccount
GetAccountsAccount.description: Retrieves the details of an account.

PostAccountsAccount.title: PostAccountsAccount
PostAccountsAccount.description:
Updates a connected account [/docs/connect/accounts] by setting the values of
the parameters passed.

PostAccountsAccountBankAccounts.title: PostAccountsAccountBankAccounts
PostAccountsAccountBankAccounts.description: Create an external account for a given account.

DeleteAccountsAccountBankAccountsId.title: DeleteAccountsAccountBankAccountsId
DeleteAccountsAccountBankAccountsId.description: Delete a specified external account for a given account.

GetAccountsAccountBankAccountsId.title: GetAccountsAccountBankAccountsId
GetAccountsAccountBankAccountsId.description: Retrieve a specified external account for a given account.

PostAccountsAccountBankAccountsId.title: PostAccountsAccountBankAccountsId
PostAccountsAccountBankAccountsId.description:
Updates the metadata, account holder name, account holder type of a bank account
belonging to a Custom account [/docs/connect/custom-accounts], and optionally
sets it as the default for its currency.

GetAccountsAccountCapabilitiesCapability.title: GetAccountsAccountCapabilitiesCapability
GetAccountsAccountCapabilitiesCapability.description: Retrieves information about the specified Account Capability.

PostAccountsAccountExternalAccounts.title: PostAccountsAccountExternalAccounts
PostAccountsAccountExternalAccounts.description: Create an external account for a given account.

DeleteAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId.title: DeleteAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId
DeleteAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId.description: Delete a specified external account for a given account.

GetAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId.title: GetAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId
GetAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId.description: Retrieve a specified external account for a given account.

PostAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId.title: PostAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId
PostAccountsAccountExternalAccountsId.description:
Updates the metadata, account holder name, account holder type of a bank account
belonging to a Custom account [/docs/connect/custom-accounts].

PostAccountsAccountLoginLinks.title: PostAccountsAccountLoginLinks
PostAccountsAccountLoginLinks.description:
Creates a single-use login link for an Express account to access their Stripe
dashboard.

You may only create login links for Express accounts
[/docs/connect/express-accounts] connected to your platform.

DeleteAccountsAccountPeoplePerson.title: DeleteAccountsAccountPeoplePerson
DeleteAccountsAccountPeoplePerson.description:
Deletes an existing person's relationship to the account's legal entity. Any
person with a relationship for an account can be deleted through the API, except
if the person is the account_opener.

DeleteAccountsAccountPersonsPerson.title: DeleteAccountsAccountPersonsPerson
DeleteAccountsAccountPersonsPerson.description: Deletes an existing person's relationship to the account's legal entity.

PostAccountsAccountReject.title: PostAccountsAccountReject
PostAccountsAccountReject.description:
With Connect [/docs/connect], you may flag accounts as suspicious.

Test-mode Custom and Express accounts can be rejected at any time.

GetApplicationFeesFeeRefundsId.title: GetApplicationFeesFeeRefundsId
GetApplicationFeesFeeRefundsId.description:
By default, you can see the 10 most recent refunds stored directly on the
application fee object, but you can also retrieve details about a specific
refund stored on the application fee.

PostApplicationFeesFeeRefundsId.title: PostApplicationFeesFeeRefundsId
PostApplicationFeesFeeRefundsId.description:
Updates the specified application fee refund by setting the values of the
parameters passed. Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

GetApplicationFeesId.title: GetApplicationFeesId
GetApplicationFeesId.description:
Retrieves the details of an application fee that your account has collected. The
same information is returned when refunding the application fee.

PostApplicationFeesIdRefunds.title: PostApplicationFeesIdRefunds
PostApplicationFeesIdRefunds.description:
Refunds an application fee that has previously been collected but not yet
refunded. Funds will be refunded to the Stripe account from which the fee was
originally collected.

GetBalanceHistoryId.title: GetBalanceHistoryId
GetBalanceHistoryId.description:
Retrieves the balance transaction with the given ID.

Note that this endpoint previously used the path /v1/balance/history/:id.

GetBalanceTransactionsId.title: GetBalanceTransactionsId
GetBalanceTransactionsId.description:
Retrieves the balance transaction with the given ID.

Note that this endpoint previously used the path /v1/balance/history/:id.

PostBillingPortalConfigurations.title: PostBillingPortalConfigurations
PostBillingPortalConfigurations.description:
Creates a configuration that describes the functionality and behavior of a
PortalSession

GetBillingPortalConfigurationsConfigurat.title: GetBillingPortalConfigurationsConfiguration
GetBillingPortalConfigurationsConfigurat.description:
Retrieves a configuration that describes the functionality of the customer
portal.

PostBillingPortalConfigurationsConfigura.title: PostBillingPortalConfigurationsConfiguration
PostBillingPortalConfigurationsConfigura.description: Updates a configuration that describes the functionality of the customer portal.

PostBillingPortalSessions.title: PostBillingPortalSessions
PostBillingPortalSessions.description: Creates a session of the customer portal.

GetBitcoinReceiversId.title: GetBitcoinReceiversId
GetBitcoinReceiversId.description: Retrieves the Bitcoin receiver with the given ID.

PostCharges.title: PostCharges
PostCharges.description: To charge a credit card or other payment source, you create a Charge object.

GetChargesCharge.title: GetChargesCharge
GetChargesCharge.description: Retrieves the details of a charge that has previously been created.

PostChargesCharge.title: PostChargesCharge
PostChargesCharge.description:
Updates the specified charge by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostChargesChargeCapture.title: PostChargesChargeCapture
PostChargesChargeCapture.description: Capture the payment of an existing, uncaptured, charge.

PostChargesChargeRefund.title: PostChargesChargeRefund
PostChargesChargeRefund.description:
When you create a new refund, you must specify a Charge or a PaymentIntent
object on which to create it.

GetChargesChargeRefundsRefund.title: GetChargesChargeRefundsRefund
GetChargesChargeRefundsRefund.description: Retrieves the details of an existing refund.

GetCountrySpecsCountry.title: GetCountrySpecsCountry
GetCountrySpecsCountry.description: Returns a Country Spec for a given Country code.

PostCoupons.title: PostCoupons
PostCoupons.description:
You can create coupons easily via the coupon management
[https://dashboard.stripe.com/coupons] page of the Stripe dashboard.

DeleteCouponsCoupon.title: DeleteCouponsCoupon
DeleteCouponsCoupon.description:
You can delete coupons via the coupon management
[https://dashboard.stripe.com/coupons] page of the Stripe dashboard.

GetCouponsCoupon.title: GetCouponsCoupon
GetCouponsCoupon.description: Retrieves the coupon with the given ID.

PostCouponsCoupon.title: PostCouponsCoupon
PostCouponsCoupon.description:
Updates the metadata of a coupon. Other coupon details (currency, duration,
amount_off) are, by design, not editable.

PostCreditNotes.title: PostCreditNotes
PostCreditNotes.description:
Issue a credit note to adjust the amount of a finalized invoice. For a 
status=open invoice, a credit note reduces its amount_due.

GetCreditNotesId.title: GetCreditNotesId
GetCreditNotesId.description: Retrieves the credit note object with the given identifier.

PostCreditNotesIdVoid.title: PostCreditNotesIdVoid
PostCreditNotesIdVoid.description:
Marks a credit note as void. Learn more about voiding credit notes
[/docs/billing/invoices/credit-notes#voiding].

DeleteCustomersCustomer.title: DeleteCustomersCustomer
DeleteCustomersCustomer.description:
Permanently deletes a customer. It cannot be undone. Also immediately cancels
any active subscriptions on the customer.

GetCustomersCustomer.title: GetCustomersCustomer
GetCustomersCustomer.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing customer. You need only supply the unique
customer identifier that was returned upon customer creation.

PostCustomersCustomer.title: PostCustomersCustomer
PostCustomersCustomer.description:
Updates the specified customer by setting the values of the parameters passed.
Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions.title: PostCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions
PostCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions.description:
Creates an immutable transaction that updates the customer's credit balance
[/docs/billing/customer/balance].

GetCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactionsT.title: GetCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactionsTransaction
GetCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactionsT.description:
Retrieves a specific customer balance transaction that updated the customer's 
balances [/docs/billing/customer/balance].

PostCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions.title: PostCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactionsTransaction
PostCustomersCustomerBalanceTransactions.description:
Most credit balance transaction fields are immutable, but you may update its 
description and metadata.

PostCustomersCustomerBankAccounts.title: PostCustomersCustomerBankAccounts
PostCustomersCustomerBankAccounts.description:
When you create a new credit card, you must specify a customer or recipient on
which to create it.

DeleteCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId.title: DeleteCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId
DeleteCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId.description: Delete a specified source for a given customer.

GetCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId.title: GetCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId
GetCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId.description:
By default, you can see the 10 most recent sources stored on a Customer directly
on the object.

PostCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId.title: PostCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId
PostCustomersCustomerBankAccountsId.description: Update a specified source for a given customer.

PostCustomersCustomerBankAccountsIdVerif.title: PostCustomersCustomerBankAccountsIdVerify
PostCustomersCustomerBankAccountsIdVerif.description: Verify a specified bank account for a given customer.

PostCustomersCustomerCards.title: PostCustomersCustomerCards
PostCustomersCustomerCards.description:
When you create a new credit card, you must specify a customer or recipient on
which to create it.

If the card's owner has no default card, then the new card will become the
default.

DeleteCustomersCustomerCardsId.title: DeleteCustomersCustomerCardsId
DeleteCustomersCustomerCardsId.description: Delete a specified source for a given customer.

GetCustomersCustomerCardsId.title: GetCustomersCustomerCardsId
GetCustomersCustomerCardsId.description:
You can always see the 10 most recent cards directly on a customer; this method
lets you retrieve details about a specific card stored on the customer.

PostCustomersCustomerCardsId.title: PostCustomersCustomerCardsId
PostCustomersCustomerCardsId.description: Update a specified source for a given customer.

DeleteCustomersCustomerDiscount.title: DeleteCustomersCustomerDiscount
DeleteCustomersCustomerDiscount.description: Removes the currently applied discount on a customer.

PostCustomersCustomerSources.title: PostCustomersCustomerSources
PostCustomersCustomerSources.description:
When you create a new credit card, you must specify a customer or recipient on
which to create it.

DeleteCustomersCustomerSourcesId.title: DeleteCustomersCustomerSourcesId
DeleteCustomersCustomerSourcesId.description: Delete a specified source for a given customer.

GetCustomersCustomerSourcesId.title: GetCustomersCustomerSourcesId
GetCustomersCustomerSourcesId.description: Retrieve a specified source for a given customer.

PostCustomersCustomerSourcesId.title: PostCustomersCustomerSourcesId
PostCustomersCustomerSourcesId.description: Update a specified source for a given customer.

PostCustomersCustomerSourcesIdVerify.title: PostCustomersCustomerSourcesIdVerify
PostCustomersCustomerSourcesIdVerify.description: Verify a specified bank account for a given customer.

PostCustomersCustomerSubscriptions.title: PostCustomersCustomerSubscriptions
PostCustomersCustomerSubscriptions.description: Creates a new subscription on an existing customer.

DeleteCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubs.title: DeleteCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId
DeleteCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubs.description:
Cancels a customer's subscription. If you set the at_period_end parameter to 
true.

GetCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscri.title: GetCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId
GetCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscri.description: Retrieves the subscription with the given ID.

PostCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscr.title: PostCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId
PostCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscr.description:
Updates an existing subscription on a customer to match the specified
parameters.

DeleteCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubs.title: DeleteCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedIdDiscount
DeleteCustomersCustomerSubscriptionsSubs.description: Removes the currently applied discount on a customer.

PostCustomersCustomerTaxIds.title: PostCustomersCustomerTaxIds
PostCustomersCustomerTaxIds.description: Creates a new TaxID object for a customer.

GetCustomersCustomerTaxIdsId.title: GetCustomersCustomerTaxIdsId
GetCustomersCustomerTaxIdsId.description: Retrieves the TaxID object with the given identifier.

GetDisputesDispute.title: GetDisputesDispute
GetDisputesDispute.description: Retrieves the dispute with the given ID.

PostDisputesDispute.title: PostDisputesDispute
PostDisputesDispute.description: When you get a dispute, contacting your customer is always the best first step.

PostDisputesDisputeClose.title: PostDisputesDisputeClose
PostDisputesDisputeClose.description:
Closing the dispute for a charge indicates that you do not have any evidence to
submit and are essentially dismissing the dispute, acknowledging it as lost.

The status of the dispute will change from needs_response to lost. Closing a
dispute is irreversible.

PostEphemeralKeys.title: PostEphemeralKeys
PostEphemeralKeys.description: Creates a short-lived API key for a given resource.

DeleteEphemeralKeysKey.title: DeleteEphemeralKeysKey
DeleteEphemeralKeysKey.description: Invalidates a short-lived API key for a given resource.

GetEventsId.title: GetEventsId
GetEventsId.description:
Retrieves the details of an event. Supply the unique identifier of the event,
which you might have received in a webhook.

GetExchangeRatesRateId.title: GetExchangeRatesRateId
GetExchangeRatesRateId.description:
Retrieves the exchange rates from the given currency to every supported
currency.

PostFileLinks.title: PostFileLinks
PostFileLinks.description: Creates a new file link object.

GetFileLinksLink.title: GetFileLinksLink
GetFileLinksLink.description: Retrieves the file link with the given ID.

PostFileLinksLink.title: PostFileLinksLink
PostFileLinksLink.description: Updates an existing file link object. Expired links can no longer be updated.

PostFiles.title: PostFiles
PostFiles.description:
To upload a file to Stripe, you'll need to send a request of type 
multipart/form-data.

GetFilesFile.title: GetFilesFile
GetFilesFile.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing file object. Supply the unique file ID from
a file.

PostIdentityVerificationSessions.title: PostIdentityVerificationSessions
PostIdentityVerificationSessions.description:
Creates a VerificationSession object.

After the VerificationSession is created.

GetIdentityVerificationSessionsSession.title: GetIdentityVerificationSessionsSession
GetIdentityVerificationSessionsSession.description: Retrieves the details of a VerificationSession that was previously created.

PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSession.title: PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSession
PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSession.description:
Updates a VerificationSession object.

When the session status is requires_input, you can use this method to update the
verification check and options.

PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSessionC.title: PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSessionCancel
PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSessionC.description:
A VerificationSession object can be canceled when it is in requires_input status
[/docs/identity/how-sessions-work].

PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSessionR.title: PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSessionRedact
PostIdentityVerificationSessionsSessionR.description:
Redact a VerificationSession to remove all collected information from Stripe.
This will redact the VerificationSession and all objects related to it.

PostInvoiceitems.title: PostInvoiceitems
PostInvoiceitems.description:
Creates an item to be added to a draft invoice (up to 250 items per invoice). If
no invoice is specified, the item will be on the next invoice created for the
customer specified.

DeleteInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem.title: DeleteInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem
DeleteInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem.description:
Deletes an invoice item, removing it from an invoice. Deleting invoice items is
only possible when they're not attached to invoices, or if it's attached to a
draft invoice.

GetInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem.title: GetInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem
GetInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem.description: Retrieves the invoice item with the given ID.

PostInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem.title: PostInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem
PostInvoiceitemsInvoiceitem.description:
Updates the amount or description of an invoice item on an upcoming invoice.
Updating an invoice item is only possible before the invoice it's attached to is
closed.

PostInvoices.title: PostInvoices
PostInvoices.description:
This endpoint creates a draft invoice for a given customer. The draft invoice
created pulls in all pending invoice items on that customer, including
prorations.

DeleteInvoicesInvoice.title: DeleteInvoicesInvoice
DeleteInvoicesInvoice.description:
Permanently deletes a one-off invoice draft. This cannot be undone. Attempts to
delete invoices that are no longer in a draft state will fail; once an invoice
has been finalized or if an invoice is for a subscription, it must be voided.

GetInvoicesInvoice.title: GetInvoicesInvoice
GetInvoicesInvoice.description: Retrieves the invoice with the given ID.

PostInvoicesInvoiceFinalize.title: PostInvoicesInvoiceFinalize
PostInvoicesInvoiceFinalize.description:
Stripe automatically finalizes drafts before sending and attempting payment on
invoices.

PostInvoicesInvoiceMarkUncollectible.title: PostInvoicesInvoiceMarkUncollectible
PostInvoicesInvoiceMarkUncollectible.description:
Marking an invoice as uncollectible is useful for keeping track of bad debts
that can be written off for accounting purposes.

PostInvoicesInvoicePay.title: PostInvoicesInvoicePay
PostInvoicesInvoicePay.description:
Stripe automatically creates and then attempts to collect payment on invoices
for customers on subscriptions according to your subscriptions settings
[https://dashboard.stripe.com/account/billing/automatic]. However, if you'd like
to attempt payment on an invoice out of the normal collection schedule or for
some other reason, you can do so.

PostInvoicesInvoiceSend.title: PostInvoicesInvoiceSend
PostInvoicesInvoiceSend.description:
Stripe will automatically send invoices to customers according to your 
subscriptions settings [https://dashboard.stripe.com/account/billing/automatic].

PostInvoicesInvoiceVoid.title: PostInvoicesInvoiceVoid
PostInvoicesInvoiceVoid.description:
Mark a finalized invoice as void. This cannot be undone. Voiding an invoice is
similar to deletion.

GetIssuerFraudRecordsIssuerFraudRecord.title: GetIssuerFraudRecordsIssuerFraudRecord
GetIssuerFraudRecordsIssuerFraudRecord.description:
Retrieves the details of an issuer fraud record that has previously been
created. 

Please refer to the issuer fraud record object reference for more details.

PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorization.title: PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorization
PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorization.description:
Updates the specified Issuing Authorization object by setting the values of the
parameters passed. Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorizationAp.title: PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorizationApprove
PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorizationAp.description: Approves a pending Issuing Authorization object.

PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorizationDe.title: PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorizationDecline
PostIssuingAuthorizationsAuthorizationDe.description: Declines a pending Issuing Authorization object.

PostIssuingCardholders.title: PostIssuingCardholders
PostIssuingCardholders.description: Creates a new Issuing Cardholder object that can be issued cards.

PostIssuingCardholdersCardholder.title: PostIssuingCardholdersCardholder
PostIssuingCardholdersCardholder.description:
Updates the specified Issuing Cardholder object by setting the values of the
parameters passed.

PostIssuingCardsCard.title: PostIssuingCardsCard
PostIssuingCardsCard.description:
Updates the specified Issuing Card object by setting the values of the
parameters passed. Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostIssuingDisputesDispute.title: PostIssuingDisputesDispute
PostIssuingDisputesDispute.description:
Updates the specified Issuing Dispute object by setting the values of the
parameters passed.

PostIssuingDisputesDisputeSubmit.title: PostIssuingDisputesDisputeSubmit
PostIssuingDisputesDisputeSubmit.description: Submits an Issuing Dispute to the card network.

PostIssuingSettlementsSettlement.title: PostIssuingSettlementsSettlement
PostIssuingSettlementsSettlement.description:
Updates the specified Issuing Settlement object by setting the values of the
parameters passed. Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostIssuingTransactionsTransaction.title: PostIssuingTransactionsTransaction
PostIssuingTransactionsTransaction.description:
Updates the specified Issuing Transaction object by setting the values of the
parameters passed. Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

GetOrderReturnsId.title: GetOrderReturnsId
GetOrderReturnsId.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing order return. Supply the unique order ID
from either an order return creation request or the order return list.

GetOrdersId.title: GetOrdersId
GetOrdersId.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing order. Supply the unique order ID from
either an order creation request or the order list.

PostOrdersId.title: PostOrdersId
PostOrdersId.description:
Updates the specific order by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostOrdersIdPay.title: PostOrdersIdPay
PostOrdersIdPay.description: Pay an order by providing a source to create a payment.

PostOrdersIdReturns.title: PostOrdersIdReturns
PostOrdersIdReturns.description:
Return all or part of an order. The order must have a status of paid or 
fulfilled before it can be returned.

GetPaymentIntentsIntent.title: GetPaymentIntentsIntent
GetPaymentIntentsIntent.description: Retrieves the details of a PaymentIntent that has previously been created.

PostPaymentIntentsIntent.title: PostPaymentIntentsIntent
PostPaymentIntentsIntent.description:
Updates properties on a PaymentIntent object without confirming.

Depending on which properties you update.

PostPaymentIntentsIntentCancel.title: PostPaymentIntentsIntentCancel
PostPaymentIntentsIntentCancel.description: A PaymentIntent object can be canceled when it is in one of these statuses:

PostPaymentIntentsIntentCapture.title: PostPaymentIntentsIntentCapture
PostPaymentIntentsIntentCapture.description:
Capture the funds of an existing uncaptured PaymentIntent when its status is 
requires_capture.

PostPaymentIntentsIntentConfirm.title: PostPaymentIntentsIntentConfirm
PostPaymentIntentsIntentConfirm.description:
Confirm that your customer intends to pay with current or provided payment
method.

PostPaymentMethods.title: PostPaymentMethods
PostPaymentMethods.description:
Creates a PaymentMethod object. Read the Stripe.js reference
[/docs/stripe-js/reference#stripe-create-payment-method] to learn how to create
PaymentMethods via Stripe.js.

PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethod.title: PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethod
PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethod.description:
Updates a PaymentMethod object. A PaymentMethod must be attached a customer to
be updated.

PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethodAttach.title: PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethodAttach
PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethodAttach.description:
Attaches a PaymentMethod object to a Customer.

To attach a new PaymentMethod to a customer for future payments.

PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethodDetach.title: PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethodDetach
PostPaymentMethodsPaymentMethodDetach.description: Detaches a PaymentMethod object from a Customer.

PostPayouts.title: PostPayouts
PostPayouts.description: To send funds to your own bank account, you create a new payout object.

GetPayoutsPayout.title: GetPayoutsPayout
GetPayoutsPayout.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing payout. Supply the unique payout ID from
either a payout creation request or the payout list, and Stripe will return the
corresponding payout information.

PostPayoutsPayout.title: PostPayoutsPayout
PostPayoutsPayout.description:
Updates the specified payout by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged. This request accepts only the
metadata as arguments.

PostPayoutsPayoutCancel.title: PostPayoutsPayoutCancel
PostPayoutsPayoutCancel.description:
A previously created payout can be canceled if it has not yet been paid out.
Funds will be refunded to your available balance. You may not cancel automatic
Stripe payouts.

PostPayoutsPayoutReverse.title: PostPayoutsPayoutReverse
PostPayoutsPayoutReverse.description:
Reverses a payout by debiting the destination bank account. Only payouts for
connected accounts to US bank accounts may be reversed at this time.

PostPlans.title: PostPlans
PostPlans.description:
You can now model subscriptions more flexibly using the Prices API. It replaces
the Plans API and is backwards compatible to simplify your migration.

DeletePlansPlan.title: DeletePlansPlan
DeletePlansPlan.description:
Deleting plans means new subscribers can't be added. Existing subscribers aren't
affected.

GetPlansPlan.title: GetPlansPlan
GetPlansPlan.description: Retrieves the plan with the given ID.

PostPlansPlan.title: PostPlansPlan
PostPlansPlan.description:
Updates the specified plan by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided are left unchanged. By design, you cannot change a
plan's ID, amount, currency, or billing cycle.

PostPrices.title: PostPrices
PostPrices.description:
Creates a new price for an existing product. The price can be recurring or
one-time.

GetPricesPrice.title: GetPricesPrice
GetPricesPrice.description: Retrieves the price with the given ID.

PostPricesPrice.title: PostPricesPrice
PostPricesPrice.description:
Updates the specified price by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided are left unchanged.

DeleteProductsId.title: DeleteProductsId
DeleteProductsId.description:
Delete a product. Deleting a product is only possible if it has no prices
associated with it. Additionally, deleting a product with type=good is only
possible if it has no SKUs associated with it.

GetProductsId.title: GetProductsId
GetProductsId.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing product. Supply the unique product ID from
either a product creation request or the product list, and Stripe will return
the corresponding product information.

PostProductsId.title: PostProductsId
PostProductsId.description:
Updates the specific product by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostPromotionCodes.title: PostPromotionCodes
PostPromotionCodes.description:
A promotion code points to a coupon. You can optionally restrict the code to a
specific customer, redemption limit, and expiration date.

GetPromotionCodesPromotionCode.title: GetPromotionCodesPromotionCode
GetPromotionCodesPromotionCode.description: Retrieves the promotion code with the given ID.

PostPromotionCodesPromotionCode.title: PostPromotionCodesPromotionCode
PostPromotionCodesPromotionCode.description:
Updates the specified promotion code by setting the values of the parameters
passed. Most fields are, by design, not editable.

PostQuotes.title: PostQuotes
PostQuotes.description: A quote models prices and services for a customer.

GetQuotesQuote.title: GetQuotesQuote
GetQuotesQuote.description: Retrieves the quote with the given ID.

PostQuotesQuote.title: PostQuotesQuote
PostQuotesQuote.description: A quote models prices and services for a customer.

GetRadarEarlyFraudWarningsEarlyFraudWarn.title: GetRadarEarlyFraudWarningsEarlyFraudWarning
GetRadarEarlyFraudWarningsEarlyFraudWarn.description:
Retrieves the details of an early fraud warning that has previously been
created. 

Please refer to the early fraud warning object reference for more details.

PostRadarValueListItems.title: PostRadarValueListItems
PostRadarValueListItems.description:
Creates a new ValueListItem object, which is added to the specified parent value
list.

DeleteRadarValueListItemsItem.title: DeleteRadarValueListItemsItem
DeleteRadarValueListItemsItem.description: Deletes a ValueListItem object, removing it from its parent value list.

PostRadarValueLists.title: PostRadarValueLists
PostRadarValueLists.description: Creates a new ValueList object, which can then be referenced in rules.

DeleteRadarValueListsValueList.title: DeleteRadarValueListsValueList
DeleteRadarValueListsValueList.description:
Deletes a ValueList object, also deleting any items contained within the value
list. To be deleted, a value list must not be referenced in any rules.

PostRadarValueListsValueList.title: PostRadarValueListsValueList
PostRadarValueListsValueList.description:
Updates a ValueList object by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged. Note that item_type is
immutable.

PostRecipients.title: PostRecipients
PostRecipients.description:
Creates a new Recipient object and verifies the recipient's identity. Also
verifies the recipient's bank account information or debit card, if either is
provided.

DeleteRecipientsId.title: DeleteRecipientsId
DeleteRecipientsId.description: Permanently deletes a recipient. It cannot be undone.

GetRecipientsId.title: GetRecipientsId
GetRecipientsId.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing recipient. You need only supply the unique
recipient identifier that was returned upon recipient creation.

PostRecipientsId.title: PostRecipientsId
PostRecipientsId.description:
Updates the specified recipient by setting the values of the parameters passed.
Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

GetRefundsRefund.title: GetRefundsRefund
GetRefundsRefund.description: Retrieves the details of an existing refund.

PostRefundsRefund.title: PostRefundsRefund
PostRefundsRefund.description:
Updates the specified refund by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

This request only accepts metadata as an argument.

PostReportingReportRuns.title: PostReportingReportRuns
PostReportingReportRuns.description:
Creates a new object and begin running the report. (Certain report types require
a live-mode API key [https://stripe.com/docs/keys#test-live-modes].)

GetReportingReportRunsReportRun.title: GetReportingReportRunsReportRun
GetReportingReportRunsReportRun.description: Retrieves the details of an existing Report Run.

GetReportingReportTypesReportType.title: GetReportingReportTypesReportType
GetReportingReportTypesReportType.description:
Retrieves the details of a Report Type. (Certain report types require a 
live-mode API key [https://stripe.com/docs/keys#test-live-modes].)

PostReviewsReviewApprove.title: PostReviewsReviewApprove
PostReviewsReviewApprove.description: Approves a Review object, closing it and removing it from the list of reviews.

PostSetupIntents.title: PostSetupIntents
PostSetupIntents.description:
Creates a SetupIntent object.

After the SetupIntent is created, attach a payment method and confirm
[/docs/api/setup_intents/confirm]

GetSetupIntentsIntent.title: GetSetupIntentsIntent
GetSetupIntentsIntent.description: Retrieves the details of a SetupIntent that has previously been created.

PostSetupIntentsIntentCancel.title: PostSetupIntentsIntentCancel
PostSetupIntentsIntentCancel.description:
A SetupIntent object can be canceled when it is in one of these statuses: 
requires_payment_method, requires_confirmation, or requires_action.

PostSetupIntentsIntentConfirm.title: PostSetupIntentsIntentConfirm
PostSetupIntentsIntentConfirm.description:
Confirm that your customer intends to set up the current or provided payment
method.

GetSigmaScheduledQueryRunsScheduledQuery.title: GetSigmaScheduledQueryRunsScheduledQueryRun
GetSigmaScheduledQueryRunsScheduledQuery.description: Retrieves the details of an scheduled query run.

PostSkus.title: PostSkus
PostSkus.description: Creates a new SKU associated with a product.

DeleteSkusId.title: DeleteSkusId
DeleteSkusId.description:
Delete a SKU. Deleting a SKU is only possible until it has been used in an
order.

GetSkusId.title: GetSkusId
GetSkusId.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing SKU. Supply the unique SKU identifier from
either a SKU creation request or from the product, and Stripe will return the
corresponding SKU information.

PostSkusId.title: PostSkusId
PostSkusId.description: Updates the specific SKU by setting the values of the parameters passed.

GetSourcesSource.title: GetSourcesSource
GetSourcesSource.description:
Retrieves an existing source object. Supply the unique source ID from a source
creation request and Stripe will return the corresponding up-to-date source
object information.

PostSourcesSource.title: PostSourcesSource
PostSourcesSource.description: Updates the specified source by setting the values of the parameters passed.

GetSourcesSourceSourceTransactionsSource.title: GetSourcesSourceSourceTransactionsSourceTransaction
GetSourcesSourceSourceTransactionsSource.description: Retrieve an existing source transaction object.

PostSubscriptionItems.title: PostSubscriptionItems
PostSubscriptionItems.description:
Adds a new item to an existing subscription. No existing items will be changed
or replaced.

DeleteSubscriptionItemsItem.title: DeleteSubscriptionItemsItem
DeleteSubscriptionItemsItem.description:
Deletes an item from the subscription. Removing a subscription item from a
subscription will not cancel the subscription.

GetSubscriptionItemsItem.title: GetSubscriptionItemsItem
GetSubscriptionItemsItem.description: Retrieves the subscription item with the given ID.

PostSubscriptionItemsItem.title: PostSubscriptionItemsItem
PostSubscriptionItemsItem.description: Updates the plan or quantity of an item on a current subscription.

PostSubscriptionItemsSubscriptionItemUsa.title: PostSubscriptionItemsSubscriptionItemUsageRecords
PostSubscriptionItemsSubscriptionItemUsa.description:
Creates a usage record for a specified subscription item and date, and fills it
with a quantity.

PostSubscriptionSchedules.title: PostSubscriptionSchedules
PostSubscriptionSchedules.description:
Creates a new subscription schedule object. Each customer can have up to 500
active or scheduled subscriptions.

GetSubscriptionSchedulesSchedule.title: GetSubscriptionSchedulesSchedule
GetSubscriptionSchedulesSchedule.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing subscription schedule. You only need to
supply the unique subscription schedule identifier that was returned upon
subscription schedule creation.

PostSubscriptionSchedulesScheduleCancel.title: PostSubscriptionSchedulesScheduleCancel
PostSubscriptionSchedulesScheduleCancel.description:
Cancels a subscription schedule and its associated subscription immediately (if
the subscription schedule has an active subscription).

PostSubscriptionSchedulesScheduleRelease.title: PostSubscriptionSchedulesScheduleRelease
PostSubscriptionSchedulesScheduleRelease.description:
Releases the subscription schedule immediately, which will stop scheduling of
its phases, but leave any existing subscription in place.

PostSubscriptions.title: PostSubscriptions
PostSubscriptions.description:
Creates a new subscription on an existing customer. Each customer can have up to
500 active or scheduled subscriptions.

DeleteSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.title: DeleteSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId
DeleteSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.description:
Cancels a customer's subscription immediately. The customer will not be charged
again for the subscription.

GetSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.title: GetSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId
GetSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.description: Retrieves the subscription with the given ID.

PostSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.title: PostSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId
PostSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.description:
Updates an existing subscription on a customer to match the specified
parameters.

DeleteSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.title: DeleteSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedIdDiscount
DeleteSubscriptionsSubscriptionExposedId.description: Removes the currently applied discount on a subscription.

GetTaxCodesId.title: GetTaxCodesId
GetTaxCodesId.description:
Retrieves the details of an existing tax code. Supply the unique tax code ID and
Stripe will return the corresponding tax code information.

GetTaxRatesTaxRate.title: GetTaxRatesTaxRate
GetTaxRatesTaxRate.description: Retrieves a tax rate with the given ID

PostTerminalConnectionTokens.title: PostTerminalConnectionTokens
PostTerminalConnectionTokens.description:
To connect to a reader the Stripe Terminal SDK needs to retrieve a short-lived
connection token from Stripe, proxied through your server.

PostTerminalLocationsLocation.title: PostTerminalLocationsLocation
PostTerminalLocationsLocation.description:
Updates a Location object by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostTerminalReadersReader.title: PostTerminalReadersReader
PostTerminalReadersReader.description:
Updates a Reader object by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any
parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

PostTokens.title: PostTokens
PostTokens.description: Creates a single-use token that represents a bank account's details.

GetTokensToken.title: GetTokensToken
GetTokensToken.description: Retrieves the token with the given ID.

PostTopups.title: PostTopups
PostTopups.description: Top up the balance of an account

GetTopupsTopup.title: GetTopupsTopup
GetTopupsTopup.description:
Retrieves the details of a top-up that has previously been created. Supply the
unique top-up ID that was returned from your previous request, and Stripe will
return the corresponding top-up information.

PostTopupsTopup.title: PostTopupsTopup
PostTopupsTopup.description:
Updates the metadata of a top-up. Other top-up details are not editable by
design.

PostTopupsTopupCancel.title: PostTopupsTopupCancel
PostTopupsTopupCancel.description: Cancels a top-up. Only pending top-ups can be canceled.

PostTransfers.title: PostTransfers
PostTransfers.description:
To send funds from your Stripe account to a connected account, you create a new
transfer object.

PostTransfersIdReversals.title: PostTransfersIdReversals
PostTransfersIdReversals.description: When you create a new reversal, you must specify a transfer to create it on.

GetTransfersTransfer.title: GetTransfersTransfer
GetTransfersTransfer.description: Retrieves the details of an existing transfer.

PostTransfersTransfer.title: PostTransfersTransfer
PostTransfersTransfer.description:
Updates the specified transfer by setting the values of the parameters passed.
Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

GetTransfersTransferReversalsId.title: GetTransfersTransferReversalsId
GetTransfersTransferReversalsId.description:
By default, you can see the 10 most recent reversals stored directly on the
transfer object, but you can also retrieve details about a specific reversal
stored on the transfer.

PostTransfersTransferReversalsId.title: PostTransfersTransferReversalsId
PostTransfersTransferReversalsId.description:
Updates the specified reversal by setting the values of the parameters passed.
Any parameters not provided will be left unchanged.

This request only accepts metadata and description as arguments.

PostWebhookEndpoints.title: PostWebhookEndpoints
PostWebhookEndpoints.description:
A webhook endpoint must have a url and a list of enabled_events. You may
optionally specify the Boolean connect parameter.

DeleteWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint.title: DeleteWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint
DeleteWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint.description:
You can also delete webhook endpoints via the webhook endpoint management
[https://dashboard.stripe.com/account/webhooks] page of the Stripe dashboard.

GetWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint.title: GetWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint
GetWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint.description: Retrieves the webhook endpoint with the given ID.

PostWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint.title: PostWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint
PostWebhookEndpointsWebhookEndpoint.description:
Updates the webhook endpoint. You may edit the url, the list of enabled_events,
and the status of your endpoint.
